1
00:00:20,140 --> 00:00:23,140
<i>I've killed 13 people up until now.</i>

2
00:00:27,610 --> 00:00:32,860
<i>I consider myself stronger</i>
<i>than any random idiot off the street.</i>

3
00:00:35,990 --> 00:00:38,910
<i>Killing is fun.</i>

4
00:00:41,410 --> 00:00:43,710
<i>Talk about the look on that face</i>

5
00:00:44,290 --> 00:00:46,040
<i>of the bratty little jarl.</i>

6
00:00:49,210 --> 00:00:50,920
<i>That's why I know…</i>

7
00:00:52,630 --> 00:00:54,470
<i>This row of enemies</i>

8
00:00:55,010 --> 00:00:56,970
<i>in front of me…</i>

9
00:01:07,100 --> 00:01:09,610
<i>I'm scared! I'm scared!</i>

10
00:01:09,690 --> 00:01:12,730
<i>Damn it! They are enjoying this!</i>

11
00:01:27,540 --> 00:01:29,040
Damn it!

12
00:01:33,920 --> 00:01:34,960
Gudmund!

13
00:01:38,840 --> 00:01:40,760
My legs…

14
00:01:43,680 --> 00:01:46,180
<i>Badger is going to be killed!</i>

15
00:01:46,890 --> 00:01:48,940
<i>I can't believe it!</i>

16
00:01:49,020 --> 00:01:52,190
<i>How can he get so close</i>
<i>to the Jomsvikings?</i>

17
00:02:03,830 --> 00:02:04,910
Boss!

18
00:02:04,990 --> 00:02:08,750
Fox! Take Badger and return to the fort!

19
00:02:11,880 --> 00:02:14,550
I'm ordering the entire army to retreat!

20
00:02:14,630 --> 00:02:18,550
You must be kidding! I can still fight!

21
00:02:19,340 --> 00:02:22,260
That's enough, Badger.
Take a look around you.

22
00:02:23,010 --> 00:02:28,350
Damn it! They need this many people to die
just to realize how unmatched they are.

23
00:02:29,350 --> 00:02:32,020
Retreat!

24
00:02:32,110 --> 00:02:35,650
-What? Retreat?
-Yes!

25
00:02:37,740 --> 00:02:40,910
Don't stay together! Spread out and run!

26
00:02:41,530 --> 00:02:44,910
Wait! My legs…

27
00:02:45,490 --> 00:02:47,410
Did you say, "retreat"?

28
00:02:47,500 --> 00:02:51,790
I did not give that order! Shame on you!

29
00:02:51,880 --> 00:02:54,630
How can you call yourselves Nordic men?

30
00:02:54,710 --> 00:02:55,630
Wait for me!

31
00:02:59,760 --> 00:03:01,380
I told you not to run away!

32
00:03:02,220 --> 00:03:06,510
Do you expect me to write off your debt
with this level of service?

33
00:03:09,980 --> 00:03:14,020
Who cares about the debt.
You are done for, Ketil.

34
00:03:16,400 --> 00:03:21,450
Does this give you a little taste
of what it's like to be poor like us?

35
00:03:22,740 --> 00:03:25,330
No matter how unfair it is,

36
00:03:25,410 --> 00:03:28,580
you shouldn't have disobeyed the king.

37
00:03:29,450 --> 00:03:33,710
Just as we obeyed you.

38
00:03:35,210 --> 00:03:38,340
Power is justice, Ketil.

39
00:03:39,170 --> 00:03:44,640
This world exists for people
who are more powerful than you.

40
00:03:53,140 --> 00:03:53,980
They're here!

41
00:04:05,160 --> 00:04:08,530
-What's wrong, Wulf?
-Your Majesty.

42
00:04:09,540 --> 00:04:14,170
A subordinate of mine
just killed a man whom I think was Ketil.

43
00:04:15,120 --> 00:04:16,460
That was a poor decision.

44
00:04:17,130 --> 00:04:19,050
Did I not order them to capture him?

45
00:04:19,670 --> 00:04:22,470
Yes, I am terribly sorry.

46
00:04:23,090 --> 00:04:24,680
I will go check on that.

47
00:04:25,720 --> 00:04:30,640
The Jomsvikings are killing those who
escape, which is also against my orders.

48
00:04:31,220 --> 00:04:34,560
-Tell Floki to stop going after them.
-Yes.

49
00:04:46,570 --> 00:04:48,990
<i>For some reason,</i>
<i>the captain is walking away.</i>

50
00:04:50,410 --> 00:04:51,830
<i>It's my chance!</i>

51
00:04:53,540 --> 00:04:54,540
<i>Go!</i>

52
00:04:57,040 --> 00:05:00,880
Be careful with the bodies.
We will return them to their families…

53
00:05:06,470 --> 00:05:08,390
Canute!

54
00:05:08,470 --> 00:05:11,890
Off with your head!

55
00:06:54,280 --> 00:06:57,950
Thorgil! Where did you come from!

56
00:07:00,330 --> 00:07:02,210
From the underworld.

57
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:08,460
What a surprise.

58
00:07:09,050 --> 00:07:11,760
Who knew you could withstand my attack.

59
00:07:11,840 --> 00:07:14,640
You've improved, Your Majesty.

60
00:07:16,220 --> 00:07:17,890
<i>My right hand is limp.</i>

61
00:07:19,020 --> 00:07:21,140
<i>Did I sprain it just now?</i>

62
00:07:21,730 --> 00:07:23,060
That's the spirit!

63
00:07:24,020 --> 00:07:26,520
That's how a commander should be!

64
00:07:40,290 --> 00:07:42,750
I'd love to play with you,

65
00:07:43,290 --> 00:07:46,710
but I'm sorry. I don't have much time.

66
00:07:47,420 --> 00:07:51,300
Let's start over. Off with your head!

67
00:08:05,900 --> 00:08:09,480
You bastard!
How dare you treat His Majesty that way!

68
00:08:17,410 --> 00:08:20,660
Die!

69
00:08:35,550 --> 00:08:38,930
Your Majesty, please hand the sword to me
and stay back!

70
00:08:39,850 --> 00:08:42,560
Damn it!

71
00:08:46,520 --> 00:08:50,480
Royal guards, head back! Protect the king!

72
00:08:54,450 --> 00:08:57,370
Damn it!

73
00:08:57,450 --> 00:08:59,450
Wait, Thorgil!

74
00:09:00,830 --> 00:09:04,710
Don't go after him, Wulf.
You are heavily injured.

75
00:09:06,120 --> 00:09:11,840
It was partly due to my carelessness,
but more than that, he is a bold man.

76
00:09:13,420 --> 00:09:15,470
I want him as my subordinate again.

77
00:09:17,640 --> 00:09:19,930
Royal guards, return to your places!

78
00:09:20,510 --> 00:09:23,140
King Canute was attacked.

79
00:09:23,220 --> 00:09:25,060
All of you, go back!

80
00:09:25,140 --> 00:09:27,940
Run! Hurry up!

81
00:09:28,560 --> 00:09:31,440
-Your Majesty!
-Your Majesty!

82
00:09:32,020 --> 00:09:33,860
What?

83
00:09:34,570 --> 00:09:38,200
Who would do…? Was it Thorgil?

84
00:09:42,870 --> 00:09:43,950
That was close.

85
00:09:48,920 --> 00:09:51,040
Master! Are you alive?

86
00:09:55,460 --> 00:09:56,300
Good.

87
00:09:57,260 --> 00:09:58,720
Those soldiers

88
00:09:59,390 --> 00:10:02,560
didn't know what the master
looked like, I guess.

89
00:10:02,640 --> 00:10:04,310
You are lucky.

90
00:10:06,060 --> 00:10:07,810
Damn, you're heavy.

91
00:10:10,770 --> 00:10:14,320
Don't even think about
taking the easy way out by dying.

92
00:10:15,400 --> 00:10:19,110
You will take responsibility
as the commander of a defeated army,

93
00:10:20,450 --> 00:10:22,580
Iron Fist Ketil.

94
00:10:39,760 --> 00:10:41,720
I hear those sounds…

95
00:10:46,930 --> 00:10:48,350
The sounds I heard

96
00:10:49,850 --> 00:10:52,900
when my village was burned down.

97
00:10:55,570 --> 00:10:59,200
<i>The sound of the world falling apart.</i>

98
00:11:02,280 --> 00:11:06,370
They are fighting a war, aren't they?

99
00:11:07,750 --> 00:11:10,620
It's okay. Don't worry.

100
00:11:11,620 --> 00:11:13,540
We're not slaves anymore.

101
00:11:14,290 --> 00:11:16,210
We will leave this farm.

102
00:11:17,590 --> 00:11:22,300
That battle has nothing to do with us.

103
00:11:27,430 --> 00:11:29,350
After we leave this place,

104
00:11:30,140 --> 00:11:32,060
where will we go?

105
00:11:36,320 --> 00:11:38,030
Let's go to my village.

106
00:11:39,740 --> 00:11:42,860
It's a bit cold, but it's a nice place.

107
00:11:46,660 --> 00:11:48,160
Are there

108
00:11:49,120 --> 00:11:51,040
slaves there?

109
00:11:52,750 --> 00:11:54,330
Is there

110
00:11:55,710 --> 00:11:57,380
war?

111
00:12:02,340 --> 00:12:04,390
There was fighting in the past,

112
00:12:05,010 --> 00:12:08,850
and I would be lying if I told you
that there will be none in the future.

113
00:12:13,270 --> 00:12:16,480
I will not go.

114
00:12:17,900 --> 00:12:22,360
I am going somewhere else.

115
00:12:25,030 --> 00:12:28,910
Gardar and the children…

116
00:12:32,910 --> 00:12:36,210
<i>I had them wait for me…</i>

117
00:12:38,500 --> 00:12:42,260
<i>because I wanted to say thank you.</i>

118
00:12:47,220 --> 00:12:53,020
Thank you, Einar and Thorfinn.

119
00:12:55,020 --> 00:12:56,900
Thank you.

120
00:13:02,280 --> 00:13:03,990
The whole time,

121
00:13:04,950 --> 00:13:10,700
it felt as though
I was lost inside a nightmare.

122
00:13:12,040 --> 00:13:14,040
I was all alone.

123
00:13:16,330 --> 00:13:17,630
<i>But…</i>

124
00:13:26,180 --> 00:13:29,430
our morning chats…

125
00:13:32,220 --> 00:13:34,180
Einar's

126
00:13:35,730 --> 00:13:37,310
stories…

127
00:13:40,520 --> 00:13:42,190
No! Arnheid!

128
00:13:43,070 --> 00:13:46,150
Stay strong! Arnheid!

129
00:13:47,030 --> 00:13:48,610
Arnheid!

130
00:13:50,120 --> 00:13:54,040
Remember you said that you were going to

131
00:13:54,120 --> 00:13:58,540
protect your unborn child? Arnheid!

132
00:14:04,340 --> 00:14:08,300
This child already went ahead of me.

133
00:14:15,930 --> 00:14:18,020
All of them died.

134
00:14:19,770 --> 00:14:22,690
All of the people who were dear to me.

135
00:14:24,280 --> 00:14:28,450
What is the point of living
any more than this?

136
00:14:31,410 --> 00:14:36,000
There is nothing here anymore.

137
00:14:38,830 --> 00:14:42,710
Why do I have to live?

138
00:14:47,340 --> 00:14:48,420
I…

139
00:14:49,930 --> 00:14:54,220
Because… to me you are…

140
00:14:59,480 --> 00:15:01,900
Arnheid.

141
00:15:02,810 --> 00:15:06,030
-Arnheid!
-Move, Einar!

142
00:15:10,570 --> 00:15:16,120
My father once taught me this method
to bring the dead back to life.

143
00:15:16,620 --> 00:15:20,290
Einar, talk to her! In a loud voice!

144
00:15:22,540 --> 00:15:25,170
Arnheid! Don't go!

145
00:15:25,790 --> 00:15:29,590
I… really like you.

146
00:15:29,670 --> 00:15:32,300
I need you!

147
00:15:33,140 --> 00:15:35,930
I want you to laugh at my stories again.

148
00:15:36,010 --> 00:15:38,560
Stay alive and once again…

149
00:15:39,730 --> 00:15:41,520
Please live with me!

150
00:15:43,230 --> 00:15:46,360
Please live!

151
00:15:59,910 --> 00:16:02,330
Einar, that's enough.

152
00:17:02,730 --> 00:17:04,440
Far to the west…

153
00:17:08,110 --> 00:17:09,980
beyond the vast sea,

154
00:17:11,070 --> 00:17:15,360
there is a land called Vinland.

155
00:17:17,700 --> 00:17:20,910
<i>The land is warm and bountiful.</i>

156
00:17:21,870 --> 00:17:26,000
<i>It is so far that neither</i>
<i>slave traders nor the flames of war</i>

157
00:17:26,500 --> 00:17:27,920
<i>can reach.</i>

158
00:17:29,000 --> 00:17:31,920
<i>There, I am sure you will be able to live</i>

159
00:17:32,800 --> 00:17:34,880
<i>without feeling any pain.</i>

160
00:17:37,590 --> 00:17:38,840
Arnheid,

161
00:17:40,890 --> 00:17:44,100
come with us to that land.

162
00:17:45,480 --> 00:17:49,480
Let's create a land of peace in Vinland.

163
00:18:13,880 --> 00:18:15,130
You guys…

164
00:18:16,050 --> 00:18:18,260
Why are you still here?

165
00:18:27,520 --> 00:18:28,770
Stop, Einar!

166
00:18:29,810 --> 00:18:31,020
Ketil!

167
00:18:32,860 --> 00:18:35,860
Because of you, Arnheid…

168
00:18:37,490 --> 00:18:40,740
I will kill you! I will kill you!

169
00:18:42,740 --> 00:18:44,450
Stop it, Einar!

170
00:18:44,950 --> 00:18:47,120
Killing the master will do nothing.

171
00:18:52,840 --> 00:18:55,590
I see… So Arnheid…

172
00:18:57,710 --> 00:18:59,340
Wake up, Einar!

173
00:19:00,010 --> 00:19:00,970
Please!

174
00:19:01,720 --> 00:19:02,720
Einar!

175
00:19:32,000 --> 00:19:33,000
Einar…

176
00:19:34,000 --> 00:19:35,460
your anger

177
00:19:36,920 --> 00:19:39,720
will not subside
even if you kill the master.

178
00:19:41,680 --> 00:19:43,680
Anger will manifest anger

179
00:19:44,800 --> 00:19:46,850
and people will keep dying. That's all.

180
00:19:48,600 --> 00:19:51,270
I was living

181
00:19:52,140 --> 00:19:53,600
that nightmare this whole time.

182
00:19:56,110 --> 00:19:58,650
Please, Einar.

183
00:19:59,780 --> 00:20:03,610
Please don't put yourself
under the same curse as me.

184
00:20:39,440 --> 00:20:40,440
Dad…

185
00:20:41,150 --> 00:20:44,320
I know. Get ready to set sail for me.

186
00:21:17,060 --> 00:21:18,190
<i>God</i>

187
00:21:18,940 --> 00:21:23,320
<i>must be watching us even as we speak.</i>

188
00:21:30,660 --> 00:21:32,160
<i>As we lose our friends,</i>

189
00:21:32,790 --> 00:21:34,750
<i>as parents and children kill each other,</i>

190
00:21:35,660 --> 00:21:37,620
<i>He is looking down upon</i>

191
00:21:38,210 --> 00:21:41,460
<i>all of that from high above.</i>

192
00:21:57,100 --> 00:21:58,310
Thorfinn…

193
00:21:58,980 --> 00:22:01,320
Wait. Where are you going?

194
00:22:01,980 --> 00:22:04,320
Wait! What are you planning to do?

195
00:22:06,030 --> 00:22:08,320
I am going to meet with Canute.

196
00:22:11,120 --> 00:22:12,530
The master was still alive.

197
00:22:13,200 --> 00:22:14,450
He's not even captured.

198
00:22:15,200 --> 00:22:17,080
It's not settled yet.

199
00:22:18,670 --> 00:22:21,750
I might be able to
prevent any more deaths.

200
00:22:22,790 --> 00:22:25,960
That's ridiculous!
Let's get away from here right now.

201
00:22:26,590 --> 00:22:29,970
Why do you have to go that far?

202
00:22:32,050 --> 00:22:33,220
Thorfinn!

203
00:22:40,770 --> 00:22:43,520
This time… This time…

204
00:22:44,230 --> 00:22:47,190
Let me finally take you back to Iceland.

205
00:22:49,240 --> 00:22:50,160
Please!

206
00:22:55,870 --> 00:22:59,870
Remember you told me a long time ago?

207
00:23:02,210 --> 00:23:04,040
<i>That our ancestors</i>

208
00:23:05,170 --> 00:23:06,380
<i>ran away</i>

209
00:23:07,300 --> 00:23:11,760
<i>to escape from the fighting</i>
<i>and ended up in Iceland.</i>

210
00:23:14,350 --> 00:23:15,560
At that time,

211
00:23:16,430 --> 00:23:17,520
I thought

212
00:23:18,520 --> 00:23:20,020
that was so uncool.

213
00:23:21,390 --> 00:23:25,190
But now, I feel so proud of them.

214
00:23:26,440 --> 00:23:27,400
Thorfinn…

215
00:23:31,200 --> 00:23:35,870
When I took a quick glance,
Canute only had about 100 soldiers.

216
00:23:37,580 --> 00:23:39,620
Even if worse comes to worst,

217
00:23:41,540 --> 00:23:44,840
I will be able to at least
come back alive.

218
00:23:56,560 --> 00:23:57,510
I'll be on the ship

219
00:23:58,270 --> 00:24:00,680
and ready to set sail at any time.

220
00:24:01,640 --> 00:24:02,730
Don't push yourself.

221
00:24:04,100 --> 00:24:06,730
We will return to Iceland no matter what!

222
00:24:08,650 --> 00:24:09,940
Thorfinn!

223
00:25:53,920 --> 00:25:55,260
<i>"Courage."</i>

224
00:25:55,340 --> 00:25:57,010
Subtitle translation by: Kiko Morita

